doc.ContractDescription: WE PROPOSE A COLLABORATION WITH THE KOREA POLAR RESEARCH INSTITUTE IN WHICH WE WILL DEPLOY GPS STATIONS AND TILTMETERS ON NANSEN ICE SHELF, WEST ANTARCTICA. THESE OBSERVATIONS SHOULD PROVIDE INSIGHT REGARDING TIDAL EFFECTS ON ICE SHELVES, INCLUDING BOTH VERTICAL FLEXURE AND MODULATION OF HORIZONTAL ICE FLOW. ANALYSIS OF THE DATA USING TWO NEWLY DEVELOPED VISCOELASTIC ICE SHELF,STREAM MODELS WILL ALLOW INFERENCE OF PHYSICAL PROPERTIES OF THE ICE AND ITS UNDERLYING BED, WITH POTENTIAL IMPLICATIONS FOR GROUNDING ZONE STABILITY. THIS PROJECT COULD REPRESENT THE FIRST STAGE IN A VALUABLE AND HIGHLY PRODUCTIVE ONGOING COLLABORATION WITH SCIENTISTS AT KOPRI.

doc.ContractDescription: THE NATIONAL SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY COUNCIL COMMITTEE ON STEM EDUCATION (COSTEM), FORMED AS PART OF THE AMERICA COMPETES REAUTHORIZATION ACT OF 2010, HAS IDENTIFIED FOUR PRIORITY AREAS WHERE FEDERAL STEM EDUCATION INVESTMENTS SHOULD BE FOCUSED. ONE OF THOSE PRIORITY AREAS IS UNDERGRADUATE STEM EDUCATION INCLUDING THE RETENTION OF UNDERGRADUATE STUDENTS INTO STEM MAJORS, ESPECIALLY STUDENTS FROM UNDERREPRESENTED GROUPS. STUDIES SUPPORTED BY THE NATIONAL SCIENCE FOUNDATION (NSF) SHOW THAT UNDERGRADUATE STUDENTS WHO PARTICIPATE IN HANDS-ON RESEARCH ARE MORE LIKELY TO PURSUE ADVANCED DEGREES AND CAREERS IN STEM. AS PART OF THIS EFFORT, THE PENNSYLVANIA SPACE GRANT CONSORTIUM (PSGC) PROPOSES A PROGRAM TO INCREASE THE RETENTION RATE OF UNDERREPRESENTED STUDENTS BY PROVIDING A PROLONGED AND MEANINGFUL RESEARCH EXPERIENCE DURING THE FIRST TWO YEARS OF THE STUDENTS UNDERGRADUATE EDUCATION. THE PROGRAM WILL FOCUS ON RECRUITING FRESHMEN AND SOPHOMORE STUDENTS FROM UNDERREPRESENTED GROUPS TO ENGAGE IN HANDS-ON STEM RESEARCH PROJECTS. THE PROGRAM IS DESIGNED TO RETAIN UNDERREPRESENTED STUDENTS IN THE STEM DISCIPLINES BY ENGAGING THEM DIRECTLY IN RESEARCH AND PROVIDING THEM WITH MENTORING AND GUIDANCE FROM FACULTY AND GRADUATE STUDENTS. OVER A TWO YEAR PERIOD, 96 UNDERREPRESENTED STUDENTS WILL BE SUPPORTED IN STEM LABORATORIES AT HIGHER EDUCATION INSTITUTIONS ACROSS PENNSYLVANIA. EACH STUDENT WILL PARTICIPATE IN A MINIMUM OF 160 HOURS OF HANDS-ON RESEARCH AND WILL RECEIVE A SCHOLARSHIP OF $500 PER SEMESTER. IN ADDITION, THE PROGRAM WILL PROVIDE AN OPPORTUNITY FOR THREE RESEARCH SCHOLARS EACH AWARD YEAR TO PARTICIPATE IN A SUMMER INTERNSHIP AT AN AEROSPACE COMPANY IN SOUTHEASTERN PENNSYLVANIA.

SINCE THE 1ST PEAK OF THESE SEDS IS TYPICALLY IN THE X-RAY BAND AND THE 2ND PEAK IS IN THE GEV/TEV BAND, SWIFT, VERITAS, AND FERMI ARE IDEAL FOR THESE STUDIES. doc.ContractDescription: ASA'S AIR QUALITY APPLIED SCIENCES TEAM (AQAST) IS MAKING A MULTI-FACETED EFFORT TO PUT SPACE-BASED INFORMATION AND RELATED OBSERVATIONAL AND MODELING DATA INTO THE HANDS OF DECISION-MAKERS AT LOCAL TO INTERNATIONAL LEVELS. NOT ONLY IS THERE A CURRENT PRACTICAL PURPOSE TO THE PROGRAM, THERE IS AN UNDERLYING GOAL TO ENHANCE THE QUALITY OF INFORMATION PROVIDED SO THAT IT WILL PAVE THE WAY TO A NEW GENERATION OF SATELLITES CAPABLE OF DELIVERING CONTINUOUS AQ DATA THROUGH GEOSTATIONARY PLATFORMS. IN NASA-SPONSORED RESEARCH OVER MANY YEARS, WE HAVE WORKED ON MODELING, DATA GATHERING/ARCHIVING AND INTERPRETIVE ASPECTS OF SATELLITE, AIRBORNE, BALLOON AND GROUND-BASED OBSERVATIONS RELATED TO AQ. THIS WORK ENCOMPASSES LOCAL (WASHINGTON, DC; HOUSTON) TO REGIONAL (NORTHEASTERN US AND CANADA) TO INTERNATIONAL (TRACE-A, SAFARI-2000, TRACE-P, INTEX-A AND B) SCALES. PRESENTLY WE ARE WORKING ON TWO ASPECTS OF AQ MODEL AND SATELLITE EVALUATION THAT WE PROPOSE TO CONTRIBUTE TO THE AQAST. FIRST, WE WILL EVALUATE AQ MODEL PERFORMANCE AS WELL AS TROPOSPHERIC SATELLITE PRODUCTS USING BALLOON AND GROUND-BASED DATA. OZONE PROFILE AND SURFACE TRACE GAS DATA WILL BE SUPPLIED TO THE AQAST. THIS WORK BUILDS ON NASA-SPONSORED RESEARCH OF THE PAST 5 YEARS AND IS LEVERAGED WITH CURRENT NASA AND INDEPENDENT WORK. SECOND, WE WILL EMPLOY ECONOMIC "VALUE OF INFORMATION" APPROACHES TO AUGMENT AQ FORECASTS, BUILDING ON RESEARCH THAT APPLIES TO THE WASHINGTON-MARYLAND-VIRGINIA REGION. ALL OUR METHODS, WHICH CAN BE APPLIED TO OTHER REGIONS WITH THE AQ TEAM, HIGHLIGHT THE NEED FOR GEOSTATIONARY SATELLITE MEASUREMENTS OF POLLUTANTS. THE PROPOSAL PRESENTS SPECIFIC OBJECTIVES AND TECHNIQUES BASED ON PAST AND PRESENT AQ RESEARCH (SECTIONS 1 AND 2). QUALIFICATIONS FOR AQAST MEMBERSHIP ARE ENUMERATED, WITH ATTENTION TO LEVERAGING OPPORTUNITIES AND COLLABORATION WITH OTHER POTENTIAL TEAM MEMBERS (SECTION 3). THE PI (AMT) WILL COORDINATE DATA DELIVERY IN NEAR-REAL TIME, ANALYSIS AND VALIDATION. THE CO-IS SUPPLY EXPERTISE IN INVERSE METHODS IN REGIONAL MODELING (SEH) AND DELIVERY OF FORECASTS AND MODEL INFORMATION TO EPA AND REGIONAL AQ DECISION-MAKERS (WFR). THE PI OFFERS TO SERVE AS THE AQAST LEADER AND A LEADERSHIP VISION IS PRESENTED (SECTION 4). OUR COLLABORATORS IN THIS EFFORT ARE CONCENTRATED IN THE MID-ATLANTIC US REGION AND HOUSTON, WHERE WE HAVE A TRACK RECORD. EXTENSION TO OTHER US CITIES IS ANTICIPATED.
